</emphasis>
in having the scutellum with a pair of large black maculae adjacent to the posterior margin of the pronotum, the male pygofer with ventral margin strongly expanded ventrally, and the aedeagus atrium with a single ventral process and shaft with several small lateroventral teeth. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Gonçalves &amp; Takiya, 2022" authorityName="Silva &amp; Gonçalves &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2022" box="[547,753,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Domahovana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="naia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[547,753,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">Domahovana naia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[759,847,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[759,847,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from the latter by apically acute male sternite VII; style with apical third longer, strongly narrowed and sinuous; and aedeagus with a median dorsal lamella on the apical third of the shaft, and apex truncate in caudal view.
</paragraph>
